===Etymology===
Latin ''[[acclamare]]''; ''[[ad]]'' + ''[[clamare]]'' to cry out. See [[claim]], [[clamor]]
===Transitive verb===
#''Rare:'' To applaud
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*A glad '''acclaiming''' train. - [[Thomson]]
#To declare by acclamations.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*While the shouting crowd / '''Acclaims''' thee king of traitors. - [[Smollett]]
#To shout; as, to '''acclaim''' my joy, to salute with great approval
